===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=豘,肫}}
{{wp|zh:豚,en:Domestic pig}}
{{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} derives {{och-l|豚|tr= {{IPAfont|*lˁunʔ}}}} from {{och-l|腯|tr= {{IPAfont|*lˁut}}|fat}}. 

Its is probably related to:
* {{och-l|彖|running pig|id=3}} and {{och-l|貒|hog badger|id=1}}, inside Chinese ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}); and 
* {{cog|hmx-mie-pro|*duŋᴮ||pig}} ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 1999}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Ratliff, 2010}}), as well as speculatively linked to {{cog|trk-cmn-pro|*toŋuz|t=pig}} and {{cog|okm|돝|tr=twòth|t=pig}} ({{zh-ref|Vovin 2011}}) outside of Chinese.

{{zh-ref|Jacques (2022b)}} favors Wang-proposed internal Chinese etymology and rejects Mienic etymology as well as relation to {{och-l|彖|tr= {{IPAfont|*l̥ˁon-s}}}}, which he thinks did not mean "running pig" at all (despite being glossed so by only ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'').

